Model Selection

  • Modeled the data by using multiple methods/classifiers
    • SVM with Linear and Radial Kernel
    • Random Forest
    • CNN (Highest Performing Model)


  • Used cross validation for SVM and Random Forest models
    • Determine best model parameters
    • Prevent over fitting
    • Voting method

Support Vector Machine

  • Created SVM models using different kernels (Linear and Radial)
  • Used the RGB values for each pixel as independent variables
  • Models are trained with the whole training set
  • RSE values are calculated using 30% of train set
  • Cross validation was used to determine best hyperplanes given the entire training set


Results for different SVMs:

Prediction Package Method RES Accuracy Score Run Time
1 e1071 SVM Radial 0.0029 0.9267 < 1 minute
2 caret SVM Linear 0.0 0.8967 ~ 5 minutes
3 caret SVM Radial 0.0 0.9417 > 15 minutes

Random Forest

  • Feature Engineering
    • Created variables related to the average R, G, and B values
    • Created variables to the proportion of R to G to B values
    • Created variables for the ranges of the R, G, and B values
    • Created variables to determine which RGB value was greatest for a certain pixel


  • Used cross validation to
    • Figure out the best mtry parameter
    • Perform voting on the test set


  • Best model accuracy was 89% using this method

Convolutional Neural Network (CNN)

  • Model matrix setup using CNN:
    • Used entire training set to train the model
    • Converted RGB data of 1200 x 3072 into 1200 x 32 x 32 x 3 matrix array for input layer
    • Changed categorical results from 1, 2, 3 to 0, 1, 2 (reverted back to 1, 2, 3 for submission)


  • CNN model setup:
    • Used 4 hidden layers
    • Used max pooling twice
    • Used 3 dropout layers (.25, .25, .5)
    • Flattened matrix pushed into dense layered for output
    • Did not use photo augmentation


  • Parameter selection:
    • Epochs = 140
    • Batch Size = 16
